Since $\overline{AC}$ and $\overline{BD}$ are both tangent to circle $A$ and circle $B$, they are congruent.  Furthermore, $\overline{CE}$ and $\overline{DE}$ are both tangent to circle $A$ and circle $B$, so they are congruent.  Thus, $ACDE$ is a kite.

